	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>17 April 5620</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I enclose you<lb/> a copy of the letter written by <persName>Mrs<lb/> Samuel Benjamin</persName> to <persName>Sir M. Cod<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> which accompanied the Bible<lb/> sent him.  The vol was beautifully<lb/> bound in blue velvet &#38; gilt edges.<lb/>  The clasps &#38; border of the covers<lb/> were of silver&#44; as was also<lb/> the shield on which were engraved<lb/> the <persName>Codrington</persName> arms.  The Bible<lb/> was enclosed in a very elegant<lb/> case of birds&#45;eye maple lined<lb/> with satin&#44; the hinges lock &#38; key<lb/> of the case were of silver</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>The binding was by <persName>Mr John Lovell</persName> <del>Lovel</del><lb/> of <placeName>Montreal</placeName>&#44; the silver work<lb/> by <persName>Mr Maisenholder</persName> of the<lb/> same place&#44; indeed all was<lb/> the work of <placeName>Montreal</placeName> mechanics<lb/> except the sheets which were<lb/> your printers.  The whole<lb/> is highly creditable to the<lb/> Canadian Daughters of <placeName>Israel</placeName><lb/> and especially so to <persName>Mrs<lb/> A Benjamin</persName> who first<lb/> proposed the Testimonial.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I will shortly send you<lb/> a copy of my Review of archaia<add>&#63;</add><lb/> a few copies of which I have had<lb/> taken off in pamphlet form.</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>As I expected I perceive the<lb/> book highly spoken of by<lb/> the chief literary &#38; scientific<lb/> journals in <placeName>Britain</placeName> &#38; <placeName>America</placeName><lb/> and a second Edition is already<lb/> called for.  2000 were printed<lb/> of the first&#8212;how long would<lb/> it be before our people would<lb/> buy up an edition of a book<lb/> particularly valuable to them.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am sorry you did<lb/> not enlarge the Occident<lb/> I do not think it is as<lb/> well liked in its present<lb/> form&#8212;but of course you<lb/> should be the best to judge.</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>Having nothing of interest to<lb/> write I close&#59; Hoping<lb/> you are well &#38; happy</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)">I remain Yrs truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><persName role="author">Abraham de Sola</persName></p>
		</body>
